In this oration, Cicero appeared for the first time upon the Rostra before the Roman people. He was already forty-one years of age, and held the important office of praetor. He spoke in support of a-bill, proposed by the tribune Manilius, conferring upon Pompey the sole command in the war against Mithridates, King of Pontus.
